name: headwind
description: An opinionated class sorter for Tailwind CSS
author: Ryan Heybourn <ryan@heybourn.com>

commands.title: Headwind: Sort Tailwind CSS Classes on Entire Workspace

headwind.defaultSortOrder.description: Sort order: A string array that determines the default sort order.

headwind.classRegex.description: An object with language IDs as keys and their values determining the regex to search for Tailwind CSS classes.

headwind.runOnSave.description: A flag that controls whether or not Headwind will sort your Tailwind CSS classes on save.

headwind.removeDuplicates.description: A flag that controls whether or not Headwind will remove duplicate Tailwind CSS classes.

headwind.prependCustomClasses.description: A flag that controls whether or not Headwind will move custom CSS classes before (true) or after (false) the Tailwind CSS classes.

headwind.customTailwindPrefix.description: If the Tailwind Prefix function is used, this can be specified here (e.g. tw-).
